hackathon-eligibility: Anyone who is a student that was accepted and competed in HackMizzou
hackathon-requirements: Please describe your app in a minimum of 3 sentences.

hackathon-prizes.prize-content: $1000 for the most innovative use of embedded hardware
Dell Venue Pro tablet for the best solution using Microsoft Azure
Microsoft Kinect for Windows V2 sensor for the best solution using Microsoft Kinect
Leap Motion controllers for the team with the best hack using Leap Motion
Tessels for each team member for the most innovative use of data aggregation (servo + 1 other module)

Interviews for internships or full-time positions for first place and either Das keyboards or Raspberry Pis. Second place gets whichever first place doesn't choose. Awarded to the best consumer advocacy app.
3 months in the Columbia incubator and a consultation with Matt Kitzi, an IP and overall legal expert for the top 2 teams
Garmin vívofit for the best fitness app.
Beats pills speakers and amazon brazen speakers for the best Android app
